Using `editor.action.quickFix`, it seems that I can only trigger the quick fix for the first token of the range. Here's an example from TypeScript:

```js
class BaseClass {
    constructor() { }
}

class SubClass extends BaseClass {
    constructor() {

    }
}
```

<img width="361" alt="screen shot 2016-12-19 at 4 40 28 pm" src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/12821956/21334144/e2e745f6-c609-11e6-8a1e-a98143db54a3.png">

The quick fix error highlights the entire constructor of `SubClass`, but I can only trigger the quick fix action when the cursor is inside `constructor`

![dec-19-2016 16-41-36](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/12821956/21334154/05cd6c8a-c60a-11e6-9b47-9569cbcd70d3.gif)

The quick fix light bulb works as expected

VS Code: 1.8.1

Why is it that the color for non-blocked text in the Markdown Preview can't be controlled by the styles.css?

This doesn't work.
```css
body {
	color: #333;
}
```
The only way I can get the color to change is through changing my VS Code color theme from dark to light. Either VS Code's color theme or UI theme is preventing the Markdown Previewer from controlling that font color via styles.css.
